Ask HN: Did something at Twitter break in the last day or so?
text:
I’m a pretty casual Twitter user but I scroll headlines now and then.

For about the past 24 hours I’ve noticed that when I access it, via browser, I see the exact same content, the same tweets in the same order.

I’ve tried scrolling really far down, and it’s just the same. Log in on a desktop, it’s the same feed, nothing is being refreshed at all, every single thing is something I’ve seen before.

That’s not how Twitter has ever worked in the past, clearly something is wrong.

Assuming it’s not just me is it reasonable to guess thay something really important under the hood is now finally broken and we are being served from a cache or something?

Curious if everyone else is seeing the same thing.
